column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) > 10

column1: Find all airlines that have fewer than 200 flights.
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Which airlines have less than 200 flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: What are flight numbers of Airline "United Airlines"?
column2: select flightno from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.airline where t2.airline = "United Airlines"
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t2.uid = t1.airline where t2.airline = "United Airlines"

column1: Which flight numbers correspond to United Airlines flights?
column2: select flightno from flights where airline = 'United Airlines'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t2.uid = t1.airline where t2.airline = "United Airlines"

column1: What are flight numbers of flights departing from City "Aberdeen "?
column2: select flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Give the flight numbers of flights leaving from Aberdeen.
column2: select flightno from flights
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Give the flight numbers of flights arriving in Aberdeen.
column2: select flightno from flights where city = 'Atlanta' and countryabbrev = 'Atlanta
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen"

column1: Find the number of flights landing in the city of Aberdeen or Abilene.
column2: select count(*) from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.city = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen" or t2.city = "Abilene"

column1: How many flights land in Aberdeen or Abilene?
column2: select count(*) from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.city = t2.airport
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Aberdeen" or t2.city = "Abilene"

column1: Find the name of airports which do not have any flight in and out.
column2: select airportname from airports except select t1.airportname from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.city = t2.destairport
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: Which airports do not have departing or arriving flights?
column2: select airportname from airports except select destairport from flights
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: Find the manager name and district of the shop whose number of products is the largest.

column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select manager_name, district from shop order by number_products desc limit 1

column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select manager_name, district from shop order by number_products desc limit 1

column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select t2.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id group by t1.shop_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which shop has the most employees? Give me the shop name.
column2: select t3.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id join employee as t3 on t1.employee_id = t3.employee_id group by t1.shop_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select t2.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id group by t1.shop_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which shops run with no employees? Find the shop names
column2: select name from shop where shop_id not in (select shop_id from employee
column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select name from shop where shop_id not in (select shop_id from hiring)

column1: For each shop, return the number of employees working there and the name of the shop.
column2: select t3.name, count(*) from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id join employee as t3 on t1.employee_id = t3.employee_id group by t1.shop_id
column3: employee_hire_evaluation | select count(*), t2.name from hiring as t1 join shop as t2 on t1.shop_id = t2.shop_id group by t2.name

column1: What is the average age of the visitors whose membership level is not higher than 4?

column3: museum_visit | select avg(age) from visitor where level_of_membership <= 4

column1: Find the id and name of the museum that has the most staff members?
column2: select t1.museum_id, t1.name from museum as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.museum_id = t2.museum_id group by t1.museum_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: museum_visit | select museum_id, name from museum order by num_of_staff desc limit 1

column1: What are the id, name and membership level of visitors who have spent the largest amount of money in total in all museum tickets?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t1.id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1
column3: museum_visit | select t2.visitor_id, t1.name, t1.level_of_membership from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id group by t2.visitor_id order by sum(t2.total_spent) desc limit 1

column1: What is the total ticket expense of the visitors whose membership level is 1?

column3: museum_visit | select sum(t2.total_spent) from visitor as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.id = t2.visitor_id where t1.level_of_membership = 1

column1: Find the number of visitors who did not visit any museum opened after 2010.

column3: museum_visit | select count(*) from visitor where id not in (select t2.visitor_id from museum as t1 join visit as t2 on t1.museum_id = t2.museum_id where t1.open_year > 2010)

column1: Find the first name, country code and birth date of the winner who has the highest rank points in all matches.
column2: select t1.first_name, t1.country_code, t1.birth_date from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id order by t2.winner_rank desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select t1.first_name, t1.country_code, t1.birth_date from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id order by t2.winner_rank_points desc limit 1

column1: What is the first name, country code, and birth date of the player with the most winner rank points across all matches?
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.country_code, t2.birth_date from rankings as t1 join players as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t1.player_id order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: wta_1 | select t1.first_name, t1.country_code, t1.birth_date from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.winner_id order by t2.winner_rank_points desc limit 1

column1: List the name and tonnage ordered by in descending alphaetical order for the names.
column2: select name, tonnage from ship order by tonnage desc
column3: battle_death | select name, tonnage from ship order by name desc

column1: List the name, date and result of each battle.
column2: select name, date, result from battle
column3: battle_death | select name, date from battle

column1: What is maximum and minimum death toll caused each time?
column2: select max(t1.killed), min(t2.injured), t2.name from death as t1 join ship as t2
column3: battle_death | select max(killed), min(killed) from death

column1: What is the average number of injuries caused each time?
column2: select count(*), avg(injured) from death group by avg(injured)
column3: battle_death | select avg(injured) from death

column1: What are the different ids and names of the battles that lost any 'Brig' type shipes?
column2: select distinct t2.id, t2.name from ship as t1 join battle as t2 on t1.ship_type = t2.id where t1.ship_type = 'Brig'
column3: battle_death | select distinct t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = t2.lost_in_battle where t2.ship_type = 'Brig'

column1: What are the ids and names of the battles that led to more than 10 people killed in total.
column2: select id, name from battle where result > 10
column3: battle_death | select t1.id, t1.name from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = t2.lost_in_battle join death as t3 on t2.id = t3.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id having sum(t3.killed) > 10

column1: What is the ship id and name that caused most total injuries?
column2: select t1.id, t1.name from ship as t1 join death as t2 on t1.id= t2.caused_by_ship_id group by t1.id order by sum(t2.injured) desc limit 1
column3: battle_death | select t2.id, t2.name from death as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.caused_by_ship_id = t2.id group by t2.id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What are the distinct battle names which are between bulgarian commander 'Kaloyan' and latin commander 'Baldwin I'?
column2: select distinct t1.name from battle as t1 join battle as t2 on t1.id = t2.b
column3: battle_death | select name from battle where bulgarian_commander = 'Kaloyan' and latin_commander = 'Baldwin I'

column1: List the name and date the battle that has lost the ship named 'Lettice' and the ship named 'HMS Atalanta'
column2: select t1.name, t1.date from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on
column3: battle_death | select t1.name, t1.date from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = t2.lost_in_battle where t2.name = 'Lettice' intersect select t1.name, t1.date from battle as t1 join ship as t2 on t1.id = t2.lost_in_battle where t2.name = 'HMS Atalanta'

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select line_1, line_2 from addresses

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.course_name, t1.course_id from courses as t1 join sections as t2 on t1.course_id = t2.course_id group by t1.course_id having count(*) <= 2

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.semester_name, t1.semester_id from semesters as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.semester_id = t2.semester_id group by t1.semester_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select department_description from departments where department_name like '%computer%'

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) = 2

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name, t1.student_id from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id group by t1.student_id having count(*) = 2

column3: student_transcripts_tracking | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.middle_name, t1.last_name from students as t1 join student_enrolment as t2 on t1.student_id = t2.student_id join degree_programs as t3 on t2.degree_program_id = t3.degree_program_id where t3.degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor'

column3: tvshow | select weekly_rank from tv_series where episode = "A love of a Lifetime";

column1: What is the TV Channel of TV series with Episode "A Love of a Lifetime"? List the TV Channel's series name.
column2: select t1.series_name from tv_channel as t1 join tv_series as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel
column3: tvshow | select t1.series_name from tv_channel as t1 join tv_series as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel where t2.episode = "A love of a Lifetime";

column1: What is the name of the series that has the episode "A Love of a Lifetime"?
column2: select tv_series.series_name from tv_series as t1 Join tv_series as t2 on t1.id = t2.series
column3: tvshow | select t1.series_name from tv_channel as t1 join tv_series as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel where t2.episode = "A love of a Lifetime";

column1: List the Episode of all  TV series showed on TV Channel with series name "Sky Radio".
column2: select episode from tv_series
column3: tvshow | select t2.episode from tv_channel as t1 join tv_series as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel where t1.series_name = "Sky Radio";

column1: What is the episode for the TV series named "Sky Radio"?
column2: select episode from tv_series
column3: tvshow | select t2.episode from tv_channel as t1 join tv_series as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel where t1.series_name = "Sky Radio";

column1: Find the production code and channel of the most recently aired cartoon .
column2: select t1.production_code, t1.channel from cartoon as t1 join tv_channel as t2 on t1.id = t2.channel
column3: tvshow | select production_code, channel from cartoon order by original_air_date desc limit 1

column1: What is the produdction code and channel of the most recent cartoon ?

column3: tvshow | select production_code, channel from cartoon order by original_air_date desc limit 1

column1: Find the package choice and series name of the TV channel that has high definition TV.
column2: select package_option, series_name from tv_channel where hight_definition_tv = 'Yes'
column3: tvshow | select package_option, series_name from tv_channel where hight_definition_tv = "yes"

column1: What is the average earnings of poker players?
column2: select avg(e
column3: poker_player | select avg(earnings) from poker_player

column1: Return the average earnings across all poker players.
column2: select avg(e
column3: poker_player | select avg(earnings) from poker_player

column1: What is the maximum number of final tables made among poker players with earnings less than 200000?
column2: select max(t1.final_table_made) from poker_player as t1 join people as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id join poker_player as t3 on t1.poker_player_id = t3.poker_player_id where t3.money_rank < 200000
column3: poker_player | select max(final_table_made) from poker_player where earnings < 200000

column1: Return the maximum final tables made across all poker players who have earnings below 200000.
column2: select max(t2.final_table_made) from poker_player as t1 Join poker_player as t2 on t1.poker_player_id = t2.poker_player_id where t1.money_rank < 200000 group by t2.final_table_made order by sum(t1.money_rank) desc limit 1
column3: poker_player | select max(final_table_made) from poker_player where earnings < 200000

column1: What are the names of poker players whose earnings is higher than 300000?

column3: poker_player | select t1.name from people as t1 join poker_player as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id where t2.earnings > 300000

column1: Give the names of poker players who have earnings above 300000.
column2: select t2.name from poker_player as t1 join people as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id
column3: poker_player | select t1.name from people as t1 join poker_player as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id where t2.earnings > 300000

column1: What is the birth date of the poker player with the lowest earnings?
column2: select t2.birth_date from poker_player as t1 join people as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id order by t1.e
column3: poker_player | select t1.birth_date from people as t1 join poker_player as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id order by t2.earnings asc limit 1

column1: Return the birth date of the poker player with the lowest earnings.
column2: select t2.birth_date from poker_player as t1 join people as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id order by t1.e
column3: poker_player | select t1.birth_date from people as t1 join poker_player as t2 on t1.people_id = t2.people_id order by t2.earnings asc limit 1

column1: What is the average earnings of poker players with height higher than 200?
column2: select avg(t1.e

column2: select avg(t1.e

column1: What are the maximum and minimum values of area codes?
column2: select max(area_code) from area_code_state group by area_code order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: voter_1 | select max(area_code), min(area_code) from area_code_state

column1: What are the distinct states and create time of all votes?
column2: select distinct t1.state, t1.created from votes as t1 join area_code_state as t2 on t1.state = t2.state
column3: voter_1 | select distinct state, created from votes

column1: What is the area code in which the most voters voted?
column2: select t1.area_code from area_code_state as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.area_code = vote_id group by t1.area_code order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: voter_1 | select t1.area_code from area_code_state as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.state = t2.state group by t1.area_code order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What are the create dates, states, and phone numbers of the votes that were for the contestant named 'Tabatha Gehling'?
column2: select t3.created, t3.state, t3.phone_number from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as
column3: voter_1 | select t2.created, t2.state, t2.phone_number from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number where t1.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling'

column1: List the area codes in which voters voted both for the contestant 'Tabatha Gehling' and the contestant 'Kelly Clauss'.
column2: select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.state join area_code_state as t3 on t1.contestant_number = t3.area_code where t1.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling' intersect select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.state join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.area_code where t1.contestant_name = 'Kelly Clauss'
column3: voter_1 | select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling' intersect select t3.area_code from contestants as t1 join votes as t2 on t1.contestant_number = t2.contestant_number join area_code_state as t3 on t2.state = t3.state where t1.contestant_name = 'Kelly Clauss'

column1: Find the id, last name and cell phone of the professionals who live in the state of Indiana or have performed more than two treatments.
column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t1.state = "Indiana" or t2.cost_of_treatment > 2
column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, last_name, cell_number from professionals where state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2

column1: Which dogs have not cost their owner more than 1000 for treatment ? List the dog names .
column2: select distinct t2.name from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t1.cost_of_treatment > 1000
column3: dog_kennels | select name from dogs where dog_id not in ( select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having sum(cost_of_treatment) > 1000 )

column1: What are the names of the dogs for which the owner has not spend more than 1000 for treatment ?
column2: select t2.name from treatments as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id where t1.cost_of_treatment > 1000
column3: dog_kennels | select name from dogs where dog_id not in ( select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having sum(cost_of_treatment) > 1000 )

column1: Which first names are used for professionals or owners but are not used as dog names?
column2: select first_name from professionals union select t1.first_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.professional_id
column3: dog_kennels | select first_name from professionals union select first_name from owners except select name from dogs

column1: Find the first names that are used for professionals or owners but are not used as dog names.

column3: dog_kennels | select first_name from professionals union select first_name from owners except select name from dogs

column1: Which professional did not operate any treatment on dogs? List the professional's id, role and email.
column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.role_code, t1.email_address from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id except select t3.professional_id, t3.role_code, t3.email_address from dogs as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.treatment_id join professionals as t3 on t2.professional_id = t3.role_code
column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, role_code, email_address from professionals except select t1.professional_id, t1.role_code, t1.email_address from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id

column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, role_code, email_address from professionals except select t1.professional_id, t1.role_code, t1.email_address from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id

column1: Which breed do the most dogs have? Give me the breed name.
column2: select breed_name from breeds group by breed_name order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.breed_name from breeds as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.breed_code = t2.breed_code group by t1.breed_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which owner has paid for the most treatments on his or her dogs? List the owner id and last name.

column1: Which owner has paid the largest amount of money in total for their dogs? Show the owner id and zip code.

column1: For model tesla, how many cylinders does the car with the least accelerate have?

column3: car_1 | select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'tesla' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: For a tesla model, how many cylinders does the version with least accelerate have?
column2: select count(*), cylinders from model_list as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.edispl = (select t2.edispl from model_list as t3 join car_makers as t4 on t3.model = t4.id group by t3.modelid order by count(*) asc limit 1)
column3: car_1 | select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'tesla' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: How many cars have a larger accelerate than the car with the largest horsepower?
column2: select count(distinct id) from cars_data where horsepower > (select max(h
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: What is the number of cars with a greater accelerate than the one with the most horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max (select accelerate from cars_data) order by horsepower desc limit 1)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: How many countries has more than 2 car makers?
column2: select count(distinct t1.countryid) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.id group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 2
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from ( select t1.countryid, count(*) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 2 );

column1: What is the number of countries with more than 2 car makers?
column2: select count(distinct t1.countryid) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.id group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 2
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from ( select t1.countryid, count(*) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 2 );

column1: How many cars has over 6 cylinders?
column2: select count(*), t1.id from cars_data as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.id = t2.c
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where cylinders > 6;

column1: For the cars with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest horsepower?
column2: select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: For all of the 4 cylinder cars, which model has the most horsepower?
column2: select t3.id from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.model = t3.id where t1.cylinders
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Among the cars with more than lowest horsepower, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the car makeid and make name.
column2: select t1.makeid, t1.makeid from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id join car_names as t3 group by t1.makeid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.makeid, t1.makeid from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.model
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: Among the cars that do not have the minimum horsepower, what are the make ids and names of al those with less than 4 cylinders?
column2: select id, t3.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id join car_names as t3 group by t3.makeid having count(*) < 4
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: What is the maximum miles per gallon of the car with 8 cylinders or produced before or in 1980?
column2: select max(t2.mpg) from cars_data as t1 join car_makers as t2
column3: car_1 | select mpg from cars_data where cylinders = 8 or year <= 1980 order by mpg desc limit 1;

column1: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor'?
column2: select t1.model from model_list as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.modelid = t2.id join car_makers as t3 group by t1.modelid having avg(t2.weight) < 3500 except select t3.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.model = t2.id join car_names as t3 on t3.makeid = t3.model where t3.model = 'Ford Motor'
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the different models wthat are lighter than 3500 but were not built by the Ford Motor?
column2: select distinct model from model_list where weight < 3500 and model not in (select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.model = t2.id join cars_data as t3 on t3.model
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: Which are the car makers which produce at least 2 models and more than 3 car makes? List the id and the maker.
column2: select maker, count(*) from car_makers group by maker having count(*) >= 2
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the ids and makers of all car makers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 cars?
column2: select t2.id, t2.maker from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t2.maker having count(*) >= 2 union select t2.id, t2.maker from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id group by t2.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the id and names of the countries which have more than 3 car makers or produce the 'tesla' model?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country where t2.maker = 'tesla' group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country where t2.maker = "3"
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'tesla';

column1: Find the lowest and highest attendance of the stadiums which some concerts happened in the years of both 2014 and 2015.
column2: select min(attendance), max(attendance) from stadium as t1 join concert as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t2.year = 2014 intersect select t1.lowest, t1.highest from stadium as t1 join concert as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t2.year = 2015
column3: new_concert_singer | select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2014 intersect select t2.name, t2.location from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2015

column2: select min(attendance), max(attendance) from stadium where year = 2014 intersect select t1.lowest, t1.highest from stadium as t1 join concert as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t2.year = 2015
column3: new_concert_singer | select t2.lowest, t2.highest from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2014 intersect select t2.name, t2.location from concert as t1 join stadium as t2 on t1.stadium_id = t2.stadium_id where t1.year = 2015

column1: What are the countries having at least one car maker? List name and id.
column2: select t1.countryname, t1.id from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: What are the names and ids of all countries with at least one car maker?
column2: select t1.countryname, t1.id from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname, t1.countryid from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 1;

column1: What is the number of the cars with horsepower more than 150?
column2: select count(*) from cars_makers where horsepower > 150
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where horsepower > 150;

column1: What is the number of cars with a horsepower greater than 150?
column2: select count(*) from cars_makers where horsepower > 150
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where horsepower > 150;

column1: What is the average weight of cars each year?
column2: select avg(weight), year from cars group by year
column3: car_1 | select avg(weight), year from cars_data group by year;

column1: Which European countries have at least 3 car manufacturers?
column2: select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country where t2.continent = "europe" group by t1.country having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What are the names of all European countries with at least 3 manufacturers?
column2: select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.continent where t2.continent = "europe" group by t1.countryid having count(*) >= 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join continents as t2 on t1.continent = t2.contid join car_makers as t3 on t1.countryid = t3.country where t2.continent = 'europe' group by t1.countryname having count(*) >= 3;

column1: What is the maximum horsepower and the make of the car models with 3 cylinders?
column2: select max(price), max(price), t1.make from car_makers as t1 join models as t2 on t1.id = t2.car_id where t2.cylinders = 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: What is the largest amount of horsepower for the models with 3 cylinders and what make is it?
column2: select max(phphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphphph
column3: car_1 | select t2.horsepower, t1.make from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 3 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Which model saves the most gasoline? That is to say, have the maximum miles per gallon.
column2: select model from cars_data group by model order by sum(miles per gallon) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: What is the car wmodel with the highest mpg?
column2: select t1.model from model_list as t1 join cars as t2 on t1.model = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id order by t2.mpg desc limit 1;

column1: What is the average horsepower of the cars before or in 1980?
column2: select avg(php) from cars_makers where year < 1980
column3: car_1 | select avg(horsepower) from cars_data where year <= 1980;

column1: What is the average horsepower for all cards produced before or in 1980?
column2: select avg(php) from cars_data where year < 1980
column3: car_1 | select avg(horsepower) from cars_data where year <= 1980;

column1: What is the average edispl of the cars of model tesla?
column2: select avg(edispl) from models where model = tesla
column3: car_1 | select avg(t2.edispl) from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t1.model = 'tesla';

column1: What is the average edispl for all teslas?
column2: select avg(edispl) from cars_data
column3: car_1 | select avg(t2.edispl) from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t1.model = 'tesla';

column1: What is the maximum accelerate for different number of cylinders?
column2: select max(elevation), count(*) from cylinders group by t1.id
column3: car_1 | select max(accelerate), cylinders from cars_data group by cylinders;

column1: What is the maximum accelerate for all the different cylinders?
column2: select max(elevation), cylinders from cars_data group by cylinders
column3: car_1 | select max(accelerate), cylinders from cars_data group by cylinders;

column1: Which model has the most version(make) of cars?
column2: select model from model_list where make = (select max(make) from cars)
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: What model has the most different versions?
column2: select model from model group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select model from car_names group by model order by count(*) desc limit 1;

column1: How many cars have more than 4 cylinders?
column2: select count(*) from cars where cylinders > 4
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where cylinders > 4;

column1: What is the number of cars with more than 4 cylinders?
column2: select count(*) from cars where cylinders > 4
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where cylinders > 4;

column1: how many cars were produced in the last two years?
column2: select count(*) from cars_makers where year = (select max(year) from cars_makers)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where year >= 2019;

column1: In the last two years, how many cars were made?
column2: select count(*) from car_makers where make = 2
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where year >= 2019;

column1: How many car models were produced by American Motor?
column2: select count(distinct t1.id) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.car_id = t2.id where t2.name = "American Motor"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What is the number of car models created by American Motor?
column2: select count(*) from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.modelid = t2.id where t2.name = "American Motor"
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker where t1.fullname = 'American motor Company';

column1: What are the names and ids of all makers with more than 3 models?
column2: select t1.maker, t1.id from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.maker having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.fullname, t1.id from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: Which distinctive models are produced by maker with the full name General Motors or weighing more than 3500?
column2: select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = "General Motors" or t2.weight > 3500
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: What are the different models created by either the car maker General Motors or weighed more than 3500?
column2: select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.maker = t2.id where t2.fullname = "General Motors" or t2.weight > 3500
column3: car_1 | select distinct t2.model from car_names as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join car_makers as t3 on t2.maker = t3.id join cars_data as t4 on t1.makeid = t4.id where t3.fullname = 'General Motors' or t4.weight > 3500;

column1: In which years cars were produced weighing no less than 3000 and no more than 4000?
column2: select year from cars_data where weight < 3000 intersect select year from cars_makers where weight < 4000
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.year from cars_data as t1 where t1.weight > 3000 and t1.weight < 4000;

column1: What are the different years in which there were cars produced that weighed less than 4000 and also cars that weighted more than 3000?
column2: select distinct year from cars_data where weight < 4000 intersect select distinct year from cars_data where weight > 3000
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.year from cars_data as t1 where t1.weight > 3000 and t1.weight < 4000;

column1: What is the horsepower of the car with the largest accelerate?
column2: select t1.pumpg from car_makers as t1 join accelerate as t2 on t1.id = t2.car_id group by t2.car_id order by sum(t2.spent) desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.horsepower from cars_data as t1 order by t1.accelerate desc limit 1;

column1: For model tesla, how many cylinders does the car with the least accelerate have?
column2: select t1.cylinders, count(*) from car_names as t1 join models as t2 on t1.id = t2.modelid where t2.speed = (select min(speed) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'tesla' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: For a tesla model, how many cylinders does the version with least accelerate have?
column2: select count(*), t1.cylinders from model_list as t1 join cars as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.edispl = (select t1.model from model_list as t1 join cars as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.edispl = "2008" group by t1.modelid order by count(*) asc limit 1)
column3: car_1 | select t1.cylinders from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t2.model = 'tesla' order by t1.accelerate asc limit 1;

column1: How many cars have a larger accelerate than the car with the largest horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(speed) from cars_data where horsepower = (select max(hph) from cars_makers)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: What is the number of cars with a greater accelerate than the one with the most horsepower?
column2: select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > (select max(accelerated) from cars_data where horsepower = (select max(pumpg) from cars_makers)
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where accelerate > ( select accelerate from cars_data order by horsepower desc limit 1 );

column1: How many countries has more than 2 car makers?
column2: select count(distinct countryid) from car_makers group by continent having count(distinct countryid) > 2
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from ( select t1.countryid, count(*) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 2 );

column1: What is the number of countries with more than 2 car makers?
column2: select count(distinct countryid) from car_makers group by countryid having count(*) > 2
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from ( select t1.countryid, count(*) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 2 );

column1: How many cars has over 6 cylinders?
column2: select count(*) from cars where cylinders > 6
column3: car_1 | select count(*) from cars_data where cylinders > 6;

column1: For the cars with 4 cylinders, which model has the largest horsepower?
column2: select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.pumpg desc limit 1
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: For all of the 4 cylinder cars, which model has the most horsepower?
column2: select t1.id from car_names as t1 join models as t2 on t1.model = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 and t2.pumpg = (select max(pumpg) from cars_data)
column3: car_1 | select t1.model from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.makeid = t2.id where t2.cylinders = 4 order by t2.horsepower desc limit 1;

column1: Among the cars with more than lowest horsepower, which ones do not have more than 3 cylinders? List the car makeid and make name.
column2: select t1.makeid, t1.makeid from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.car_id = t2.id where t2.pumpg > 3 except select t1.makeid, t1.makeid from car_names as t1 join cars_data as t2 on t1.car_id = t2.id where t2.pumpg > 3
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: Among the cars that do not have the minimum horsepower, what are the make ids and names of al those with less than 4 cylinders?
column2: select id, make from cars_names where mpg = (select min(pumpg) from cars_data) and cylinders < 4
column3: car_1 | select t2.makeid, t2.make from cars_data as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.id = t2.makeid where t1.horsepower > (select min(horsepower) from cars_data) and t1.cylinders <= 3;

column1: What is the maximum miles per gallon of the car with 8 cylinders or produced before or in 1980?
column2: select max(miles per gallon) from cars_data where cylinders < 1980
column3: car_1 | select mpg from cars_data where cylinders = 8 or year <= 1980 order by mpg desc limit 1;

column1: Which models are lighter than 3500 but not built by the 'Ford Motor'?
column2: select model from model_list where weight < 3500 except select model from car_makers where model = 'Ford Motor'
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the different models wthat are lighter than 3500 but were not built by the Ford Motor?
column2: select distinct model from model_list where weight < 3500 except select distinct model from car_makers where model = "Ford"
column3: car_1 | select distinct t1.model from model_list as t1 join car_names as t2 on t1.model = t2.model join cars_data as t3 on t2.makeid = t3.id join car_makers as t4 on t1.maker = t4.id where t3.weight < 3500 and t4.fullname!= 'Ford motor Company';

column1: What are the name of the countries where there is not a single car maker?
column2: select countryname from countries where countryid not in (select countryid from car_makers)
column3: car_1 | select countryname from countries except select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country;

column1: What are the names of the countries with no car makers?
column2: select countryname from countries where countryid not in (select countryid from car_makers)
column3: car_1 | select countryname from countries except select t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country;

column1: Which are the car makers which produce at least 2 models and more than 3 car makes? List the id and the maker.
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.car_id group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.car_id group by t1.id having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the ids and makers of all car makers that produce at least 2 models and make more than 3 cars?
column2: select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.car_id group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join models as t2 on t1.car_id = t2.id group by t1.id having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker group by t1.id having count(*) >= 2 intersect select t1.id, t1.maker from car_makers as t1 join model_list as t2 on t1.id = t2.maker join car_names as t3 on t2.model = t3.model group by t1.id having count(*) > 3;

column1: What are the id and names of the countries which have more than 3 car makers or produce the 'tesla' model?
column2: select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid where t2.maker = 'tesla' union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'tesla';

column1: What are the ids and names of all countries that either have more than 3 car makers or produce teslas?
column2: select t1.id, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.countryid where t2.maker = "Telas"
column3: car_1 | select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*) > 3 union select t1.countryid, t1.countryname from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid = t2.country join model_list as t3 on t2.id = t3.maker where t3.model = 'tesla';

column1: Which country does Airline "JetBlue" belong to?
column2: select country from airlines where airline = 'JetBlue'
column3: flight_2 | select country from airlines where airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: What country is Jetblue affiliated with?
column2: select country from airlines where abbreviation = 'JetBlue Airways'
column3: flight_2 | select country from airlines where airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: List all american airline names and their abbreviations.
column2: select t1.airport, t1.abbreviation from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t1.abbreviation = 'American Airlines'
column3: flight_2 | select airline, abbreviation from airlines where country = "USA"

column1: What are american airline names and abbreviations for airlines?
column2: select t1.airportname, t1.abbreviation from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t1.abbreviation = 'American Airlines'
column3: flight_2 | select airline, abbreviation from airlines where country = "USA"

column1: How many flights have destination ATO?
column2: select count(*) from flights where airportcode = 'ATO'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights where destairport = "ATO"

column1: Count the number of flights into ATO.
column2: select count(*) from flights where airportcode = 'ATO'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights where destairport = "ATO"

column1: How many flights arriving in Jackson city?
column2: select count(*) from flights where city = "Janessa"
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Jackson"

column1: Return the number of flights arriving in Jackson.
column2: select count(*) from flights where country = 'Janessa'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Jackson"

column1: How many flights depart from City 'Syracuse' and have destination City 'Ashley'?
column2: select count(*) from flights where city = 'Syracuse' and city = 'Ashley'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airports as t3 on t1.sourceairport = t3.airportcode where t2.city = "Ashley" and t3.city = "Syracuse"

column1: How many flights fly from Syracuse to Ashley?
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport where t2.city = 'Staford' and t2.airportname = 'Ashley'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airports as t3 on t1.sourceairport = t3.airportcode where t2.city = "Ashley" and t3.city = "Syracuse"

column1: How many flights does airline 'JetBlue' have?
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t1.abbreviation = 'JetBlue'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid where t2.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: Give the number of Jetblue flights.
column2: select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t1.abbreviation = 'JetBlue Airways'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airline = t2.uid where t2.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t2.airline = t1.uid where t1.airline = "JetBlue Airways" and t2.destairport = "ASY"

column1: Count the number of JetBlue flights arriving in ASY Airport.
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport where t2.airportcode = 'ASY'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t2.airline = t1.uid where t1.airline = "JetBlue Airways" and t2.destairport = "ASY"

column1: How many 'JetBlue' flights depart from Airport 'AHD'?

column1: Return the number of JetBlue flights leaving from AHD Airport.
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'AHD'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t2.airline = t1.uid where t1.airline = "JetBlue Airways" and t2.sourceairport = "AHD"

column1: How many JetBlue flights go to City 'Aberdeen'?
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport where t2.city = 'Aberdeen'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airlines as t3 on t3.uid = t1.airline where t2.city = "Aberdeen" and t3.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: Count the number of JetBlue flights that arrive in Aberdeen.
column2: select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.airport = t2.destairport where t2.city = 'Aberdeen'
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode join airlines as t3 on t3.uid = t1.airline where t2.city = "Aberdeen" and t3.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: Which city has most number of arriving flights?
column2: select city from flights group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which city has the most frequent destination airport?
column2: select city from airport group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which city has most number of departing flights?
column2: select city from flights group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which city is the most frequent source airport?
column2: select city from airports group by city order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.city from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.city order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the code of airport that has the highest number of flights?
column2: select airportcode from flights group by airportcode order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the airport code of the airport with the most flights?
column2: select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What is the code of airport that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select airportcode from flights group by airportcode order by count(*) limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Give the code of the airport with the least flights.
column2: select airportcode from flights group by airportcode order by count(*) asc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airportcode from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airportcode = t2.destairport or t1.airportcode = t2.sourceairport group by t1.airportcode order by count(*) limit 1

column1: Which airline has most number of flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: What airline serves the most flights?
column2: select t2.aircraft from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport group by t2.airport order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Find the abbreviation and country of the airline that has fewest number of flights?
column2: select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport group by t2.uid order by count(*) limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: What is the abbreviation of the airilne has the fewest flights and what country is it in?
column2: select abbreviation, country from flights group by countryabbrev order by count(*) limit 1
column3: flight_2 | select t1.abbreviation, t1.country from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline order by count(*) limit 1

column1: What are airlines that have some flight departing from airport 'AHD'?
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'AHD'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "AHD"

column1: Which airlines have a flight with source airport AHD?
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.sourceairport = 'AHD'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "AHD"

column1: What are airlines that have flights arriving at airport 'AHD'?
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'AHD'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.destairport = "AHD"

column1: Which airlines have a flight with destination airport AHD?
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'AHD'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.destairport = "AHD"

column1: Find all airlines that have flights from both airports 'APG' and 'CVO'.
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'APG' intersect select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'CVO'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "APG" intersect select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "CVO"

column1: Which airlines have departing flights from both APG and CVO airports?
column2: select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airportcode = 'APG' intersect select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport where t2.destairport = 'CVO'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "APG" intersect select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "CVO"

column1: Find all airlines that have flights from airport 'CVO' but not from 'APG'.
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'CVO' except select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airport = 'APG'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "CVO" except select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "APG"

column1: Which airlines have departures from CVO but not from APG airports?
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport where t2.airport = "CVO" except select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airport where t2.airport = "APG"
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "CVO" except select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline where t2.sourceairport = "APG"

column1: Find all airlines that have at least 10 flights.
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport group by t2.uid having count(*) >= 10
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) > 10

column1: Which airlines have at least 10 flights?
column2: select t1.aircraft from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airport group by t1.uid having count(*) >= 10
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) > 10

column1: Find all airlines that have fewer than 200 flights.
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: Which airlines have less than 200 flights?
column2: select airline from flights group by airline having count(*) < 200
column3: flight_2 | select t1.airline from airlines as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.uid = t2.airline group by t1.airline having count(*) < 200

column1: What are flight numbers belonging to "JetBlue"?
column2: select flightno from flights where abbreviation = "JetBlue"
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t2.uid = t1.airline where t2.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: Which flight numbers correspond to JetBlue flights?
column2: select flightno from flights where abbreviation = "JetBlue"
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airlines as t2 on t2.uid = t1.airline where t2.airline = "JetBlue Airways"

column1: Give the flight numbers of flights landing at APG.
column2: select flightno from flights where airportcode = 'APG'
column3: flight_2 | select flightno from flights where destairport = "APG"

column1: What are flight numbers of flights departing from "Jackson"?
column2: select flightno from flights where flight from "Jackson"
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.sourceairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Jackson"

column1: What are flight numbers of flights arriving at "Jackson"?
column2: select flightno from flights where airport = "Jackson"
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Jackson"

column1: Give the flight numbers of flights arriving in Jackson.
column2: select flightno from flights where country = 'Janessa'
column3: flight_2 | select t1.flightno from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Jackson"

column1: Find the number of flights landing in the  Syracuse or Jackson.
column2: select count(*) from flights where city = "Sylvania" or city = "Janessa"
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Syracuse" or t2.city = "Jackson"

column1: How many flights land in Syracuse or Jackson?
column2: select count(*) from flights where city = "Sylvania" or city = "Janessa"
column3: flight_2 | select count(*) from flights as t1 join airports as t2 on t1.destairport = t2.airportcode where t2.city = "Syracuse" or t2.city = "Jackson"

column1: Which airports do not have departing or arriving flights?
column2: select airportname from airports except select t1.airport from airports as t1 join flights as t2 on t1.airport = t2.airportport
column3: flight_2 | select airportname from airports where airportcode not in (select sourceairport from flights union select destairport from flights)

column1: Show the name with template id of documents with description with the letter 'w' in it?

column3: cre_Doc_Template_Mgt | select document_name, template_id from documents where document_description like "%w%"

column1: Find both player names in each match.
column2: select t1.player_name, t2.player_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.player_name
column3: wta_1 | select loser_name, winner_name from matches

column1: Give me both player names in each match?
column2: select t1.player_name, t2.player_name from players as t1 join matches as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id
column3: wta_1 | select loser_name, winner_name from matches

column1: Find both player ages in each match.
column2: select t1.age, t2.match_name from matches as t1 join players as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.match_age
column3: wta_1 | select winner_age, loser_age from matches

column1: Give me both player ages in each match.
column2: select t1.age, t2.match_age from matches as t1 join players as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.match_age

column1: What are the average loser and winner ages across matches?
column2: select avg(loser_age), avg(winning_age) from matches
column3: wta_1 | select avg(loser_age), avg(winner_age) from matches

column1: Find their all average rank including winner and loser in each matches.
column2: select avg(t1.rank), t2.winner_rank from matches as t1 join rankings as t2 on t1.winning_id = t2.winner_ioc group by t2.winner_rank
column3: wta_1 | select avg(winner_rank), avg(loser_rank) from matches

column1: What is the average rank for all players including winner and loser in all matches?

column3: wta_1 | select avg(winner_rank), avg(loser_rank) from matches

column1: Find the highest rank of all players including winner and loser in all matches.
column2: select max(t2.rank_rank), t2.winner_rank from matches as t1 join players as t2 on t1.player_id = t2.player_id group by t2.winner_rank order by count(*) desc limit 1

column3: dog_kennels | select t1.professional_id, t1.home_phone, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) >= 2

column1: What is the name of the breed with the most abandoned dogs?
column2: select t2. breed_name from abandoned_yn as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.dog_id = t2.dog_id group by t2. breed_code order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.breed_name from breeds as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.breed_code = t2.breed_code where abandoned_yn = 1 group by t1.breed_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which breed do the most abandoned dogs have? Give me the breed name.

column1: Which owner has paid for the most treatments on his or her dogs? List the owner id and last name.

column2: select treatment_type_description from treatments group by treatment_type_code order by sum(cost_of_treatment) asc limit 1

column2: select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t1.state = "Indiana" or t2.cost_of_treatment > 2
column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, last_name, cell_number from professionals where state = 'Indiana' union select t1.professional_id, t1.last_name, t1.cell_number from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id group by t1.professional_id having count(*) > 2

column1: Which dogs have not cost their owner more than 1000 for treatment ? List the dog names .
column2: select name from dogs where dog_id not in (select dog_id from treatments) and cost_of_treatment > 1000
column3: dog_kennels | select name from dogs where dog_id not in ( select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having sum(cost_of_treatment) > 1000 )

column1: What are the names of the dogs for which the owner has not spend more than 1000 for treatment ?

column3: dog_kennels | select name from dogs where dog_id not in ( select dog_id from treatments group by dog_id having sum(cost_of_treatment) > 1000 )

column1: Which first names are used for professionals or owners but are not used as dog names?

column3: dog_kennels | select first_name from professionals union select first_name from owners except select name from dogs

column1: Which professional did not operate any treatment on dogs? List the professional's id, role and email.

column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, role_code, email_address from professionals except select t1.professional_id, t1.role_code, t1.email_address from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id

column3: dog_kennels | select professional_id, role_code, email_address from professionals except select t1.professional_id, t1.role_code, t1.email_address from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id

column1: Which breed do the most dogs have? Give me the breed name.
column2: select breed_name from breeds group by breed_name order by count(*) desc limit 1
column3: dog_kennels | select t1.breed_name from breeds as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.breed_code = t2.breed_code group by t1.breed_name order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which owner has paid for the most treatments on his or her dogs? List the owner id and last name.

column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column3: dog_kennels | select t1.owner_id, t1.last_name from owners as t1 join dogs as t2 on t1.owner_id = t2.owner_id join treatments as t3 on t2.dog_id = t3.dog_id group by t1.owner_id order by count(*) desc limit 1

column1: Which owner has paid the largest amount of money in total for their dogs? Show the owner id and zip code.

column1: Find the owner id and zip code of the owner who spent the most money in total for his or her dogs.

column1: What are the first name and last name of the professionals who have done treatment with cost below average?
column2: select t2.first_name, t2.last_name from treatments as t1 join professionals as t2 on t1.professional_id = t2.professional_id where t1.cost_of_treatment < (select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments)
column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 where cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments )

column3: dog_kennels | select distinct t1.first_name, t1.last_name from professionals as t1 join treatments as t2 where cost_of_treatment < ( select avg(cost_of_treatment) from treatments )
